                                                    <h3>Family Bauhinia officially raised the roof this week! From soulful piano and saxophone riffs to a rock band that nearly blew the speakers, our musicians brought the house down. The energy stayed high with electric street dance and pro-level yoyo act that defied the laws of physics with some seriously elite tricks. <br><br>The “mind-blowing” award goes to our specialists: a flawless recital of 200 digits of Pi and two students solving Rubik’s cubes one-handed with impossible speed. Whether shredding on a guitar or speed-cubing under pressure, our performers proved that Bauhinia has some serious range. <br><br>Huge props to everyone who stepped into the spotlight—you made us incredibly proud! 🌟🎤🎸</h3>
