                        <a href="https://www.facebook.com/187952374670085_1376226457850124" target="_blank" class="comment">Comment</a>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
            <div class="lightbox" data-id="154">
            <div class="lightbox-wrapper">
                <button class="close"></button>
                <div class="lightbox-container">
                    <time>12/02/2026</time>
                    <div class="lightbox-content">
                                                    <h3>Student Achievements of the Week” celebrates the diverse talents and hard work of the South Island School community.<br><br>From academic milestones and classroom projects to sports finishes and extracurricular contributions, we are highlighting the individual and collective successes that happen every day across our year groups.<br>- - -<br><br>Katniss (Y7) came Runner-up in the Hong Kong skateboarding open competition took place in Fanling Skatepark, 25 January 2026.<br><br>Andre, Anton, Declan, Liam, Xander & Ronni played a pivotal role and won the HK China Rugby Youth U12 Boys League and the Grand Final<br><br>Aidan, Chester & Alyssa participated in the community mural event at the Harmony Manor Services Center in Shatin organised by the Rotary Club of Buttery Valley<br><br>Blake (Y8) participated in the Hong Kong China Swimming Association Age Group Division 1 Short Course Competition and brought home three gold medals in the 50m Butterfly, 100m Butterfly, and 200m Individual Medley, plus a strong SILVER in the 100m Backstroke<br><br>Warrick (Y8) Performed his fourth consecutive performance at Rocktone Music School’s annual concert<br><br>Chloe (Y9) who recently represented Hong Kong on the world stage at the FIDE World Rapid and Blitz Championship in Doha Chloe followed this international success by dominating the HKSAR Junior Championship (3rd-4th Jan). Competing in the U14 category, she secured 6 wins out of 7 matches to be crowned the Overall National Champion.<br><br>Hilary (Y12) represented South Island School by participating in the 62nd School Dance Festival for the category of “Jazz / Street Dance (Secondary Section)” and received an Honours Award.<br><br>Royden (Y9) and Kayley (Y7) have been selected for the Development Squad of the Ski Association of Hong Kong, China (SAHK).</h3>
                                                                            <div class="gallery">
                                <div class="gallery-container">
                                                                            <div class="gallery-item">
                                                                                            <img src="/cache/img/82a318c843b53b470cea538b25322dc6.jpg" alt="629777161_18099237391928168_799909232960631193_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                                                                                    </div>
                                                                            <div class="gallery-item">
                                                                                            <img src="/cache/img/85682258a3beabd30ea508bc267f84df.jpg" alt="627924322_18099237394928168_8463532297617542670_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                                                                                    </div>
                                                                    </div>
